Cape Town - South Africa recorded a total of 1 853 new Covid-19 infections on Thursday, the National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD) daily report reveals. “Today the institute reports 1 853 new Covid-19 cases that have been identified in South Africa, which brings the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases to 3 679 539,” the NICD said. 78% of the country’s new infections on Thursday were identified in Gauteng, Western Cape and KwaZulu Natal - South Africa’s most populated provinces. A total of 28 302 tests were conducted, which represents a positivity rate of 6.5% when the number of new infections are considered. “Due to the ongoing audit exercise by the National Department of Health (NDoH), there may be a backlog of Covid-19 mortality cases reported. Today, the NDoH reports 41 deaths, and of these, 2 occurred in the past 24 – 48 hours,” the institute adds. The newly recorded Covid-19 related deaths brings South Africa’s cumulative fatalities to 99 499. NICD states an additional 65 hospital admissions occurred in the last 24 hours. Currently admitted patients per day: Meanwhile, the number of vaccines administered in the last 24 hours (107 341) increased compared to the total number recorded on Wednesday (104 643) - Gauteng continues to administer more vaccines on a daily basis than any other province. IOL